WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.500 --> 00:00:04.220
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:04.220 --> 00:00:06.650
- Good evening.

00:00:06.650 --> 00:00:08.850
Yes.

00:00:08.850 --> 00:00:11.460
And welcome to the
Radcliffe Institute

00:00:11.460 --> 00:00:15.510
for Advanced Study at
Harvard University.

00:00:15.510 --> 00:00:19.290
As Faculty Director for the
Humanities at the Institute,

00:00:19.290 --> 00:00:24.120
I'd like to both thank you
and to congratulate you

00:00:24.120 --> 00:00:26.190
for coming to this
event, which I

00:00:26.190 --> 00:00:28.650
think will not only
be illuminating,

00:00:28.650 --> 00:00:32.310
but also great fun.

00:00:32.310 --> 00:00:37.850
My name is Shigehisa
Kuriyama, but only for a few

00:00:37.850 --> 00:00:38.630
more minutes.

00:00:38.630 --> 00:00:41.080
[LAUGHTER]

00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:44.050
For over the course
of the next two hours,

00:00:44.050 --> 00:00:49.900
I've been given the opportunity
to become someone else, someone

00:00:49.900 --> 00:00:56.380
new, someone whom I've never
known in my 64 years on Earth--

00:00:56.380 --> 00:00:58.180
[LAUGHTER]

00:00:58.180 --> 00:01:00.310
--and yet someone who
has doubtless been

00:01:00.310 --> 00:01:07.050
within me all along, waiting
for this evening with you

00:01:07.050 --> 00:01:11.410
and the magic of talented
transformation artists, who

00:01:11.410 --> 00:01:14.540
are with us tonight.

00:01:14.540 --> 00:01:16.340
So tonight you'll get
a chance to witness

00:01:16.340 --> 00:01:21.020
this transformation live
not only in me, but also

00:01:21.020 --> 00:01:23.634
in Professor Robin Bernstein--

00:01:23.634 --> 00:01:26.660
[APPLAUSE] --current
Radcliffe fellow

00:01:26.660 --> 00:01:28.940
and Chair of the
Department of Women's

00:01:28.940 --> 00:01:31.940
Sexuality and Gender
here at Harvard,

00:01:31.940 --> 00:01:36.380
and was gamely agreed to
join me in this adventure.

00:01:39.020 --> 00:01:41.197
Harvard professors in drag.

00:01:41.197 --> 00:01:42.600
[LAUGHTER]

00:01:42.600 --> 00:01:45.292
Who'd have thought it?

00:01:45.292 --> 00:01:47.130
[CHEERS]

00:01:47.130 --> 00:01:51.300
But then again, why not?

00:01:51.300 --> 00:01:52.890
It's an experiment.

00:01:52.890 --> 00:01:58.260
And frankly, nobody knows how
exactly it's going to turn out.

00:01:58.260 --> 00:02:01.920
But as you track our
gradual metamorphosis

00:02:01.920 --> 00:02:05.340
into people whose gender
will probably seem much less

00:02:05.340 --> 00:02:09.060
clear than they
seem right now, I'd

00:02:09.060 --> 00:02:12.640
like you to bear
three things in mind.

00:02:12.640 --> 00:02:14.730
The first, and probably
most important,

00:02:14.730 --> 00:02:18.810
is that Robin and I
are basically you.

00:02:18.810 --> 00:02:21.030
We're merely stand-ins.

00:02:21.030 --> 00:02:24.510
And in observing the changes
that we are undergoing,

00:02:24.510 --> 00:02:30.340
you have to imagine
yourselves being transformed.

00:02:30.340 --> 00:02:33.000
You must imagine
yourselves exploring

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:37.530
the possible selves within
you that have not yet

00:02:37.530 --> 00:02:40.670
been realized.

00:02:40.670 --> 00:02:43.490
The second point that I'd
like you to think about

00:02:43.490 --> 00:02:48.710
is the remarkable power of
the art form known as drag

00:02:48.710 --> 00:02:54.410
to spotlight the enthralling
complexity of human identity,

00:02:54.410 --> 00:02:58.940
how the many different
permutations of sex, sexuality,

00:02:58.940 --> 00:03:03.590
and gender take on
infinite gradations

00:03:03.590 --> 00:03:06.590
as they become combined
with the performance

00:03:06.590 --> 00:03:10.330
and the communication of gender.

00:03:10.330 --> 00:03:15.310
This is one of the central
lessons of the wonderful 2017

00:03:15.310 --> 00:03:19.360
documentary called Kings,
Queens, &amp; In-Betweens,

00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:23.830
around which this evening's
activities are organized.

00:03:23.830 --> 00:03:26.800
And we're privileged and
delighted to be joined

00:03:26.800 --> 00:03:30.910
this evening by Gabrielle and
Jen Burton, two of the five

00:03:30.910 --> 00:03:35.530
sisters who produced this
film, as well as five drag

00:03:35.530 --> 00:03:37.390
performers, some of
whom actually you'll

00:03:37.390 --> 00:03:39.760
see in the film.

00:03:39.760 --> 00:03:41.740
So here's the
trailer for the film.

