00:23:32.090 --> 00:23:33.440
- Thanks.

00:23:33.440 --> 00:23:35.720
This conference is about
gender and communication.

00:23:35.720 --> 00:23:37.700
And we're so happy to
be here with Kings,

00:23:37.700 --> 00:23:40.790
Queens, &amp; In-Betweens and
some of the performers

00:23:40.790 --> 00:23:41.750
who were in it.

00:23:41.750 --> 00:23:44.000
It took us over six years
to make the movie because we

00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:45.410
wanted to get it right.

00:23:45.410 --> 00:23:47.913
And in our film
company, we sisters

00:23:47.913 --> 00:23:49.580
have often thought
about the issues that

00:23:49.580 --> 00:23:54.050
are communicated through media
about gender, what subconscious

00:23:54.050 --> 00:23:56.570
and conscious
messaging is telling us

00:23:56.570 --> 00:23:58.520
through those images.

00:23:58.520 --> 00:24:01.530
There is a fundamental
question about identity,

00:24:01.530 --> 00:24:04.760
how we communicate
identity beyond words

00:24:04.760 --> 00:24:07.280
and how our cultural
presumptions, stereotypes,

00:24:07.280 --> 00:24:09.140
and traditions play
into that, either

00:24:09.140 --> 00:24:13.310
influencing or reinforcing
what is being communicated.

00:24:13.310 --> 00:24:14.990
Drag shakes all that up.

00:24:14.990 --> 00:24:17.060
It shakes up a binary
system that is often

00:24:17.060 --> 00:24:19.280
imposed upon our thinking.

00:24:19.280 --> 00:24:21.470
Drag makes us
question what we see,

00:24:21.470 --> 00:24:24.470
what we perceive in the
layers of what we might know

00:24:24.470 --> 00:24:27.470
or what we actually
think we know.

00:24:27.470 --> 00:24:29.510
The communication of
gender within drag

00:24:29.510 --> 00:24:31.330
is completely up for grabs.

00:24:31.330 --> 00:24:35.210
Now, not literally, though
that does happen at some shows.

00:24:35.210 --> 00:24:38.630
But gender and identity and drag
are not defined or communicated

00:24:38.630 --> 00:24:42.140
through clothing, hair
quaffing, or other indicators

00:24:42.140 --> 00:24:44.180
that we typically stereotype.

00:24:44.180 --> 00:24:46.460
Drag uses its art
form to shake up

00:24:46.460 --> 00:24:50.530
the whole idea of what it
means to be female or male.

00:24:50.530 --> 00:24:53.250
And within an LGBTQ
performing space,

00:24:53.250 --> 00:24:56.300
it also raises questions of
how we communicate sexuality.

00:24:56.300 --> 00:24:58.790
Is it on the surface?

00:24:58.790 --> 00:25:02.630
Is it in our swagger
or in our engagement

00:25:02.630 --> 00:25:04.970
with an audience
who knows perhaps

00:25:04.970 --> 00:25:08.300
how we represent ourselves
outside of that space?

00:25:08.300 --> 00:25:10.880
Recently, the #MeToo movement
has brought communication

00:25:10.880 --> 00:25:12.920
and gender to the
forefront, gathering

00:25:12.920 --> 00:25:15.050
the strengths of millions
of individual voices

00:25:15.050 --> 00:25:18.290
and amplifying their gendered
experiences, helping them to be

00:25:18.290 --> 00:25:21.650
heard as a group, in strength.

00:25:21.650 --> 00:25:24.110
Ultimately, for Jen and
me, all the performers

00:25:24.110 --> 00:25:26.720
of this who are here
tonight, questioning

00:25:26.720 --> 00:25:30.157
these assumptions is the
key, questioning ourselves

00:25:30.157 --> 00:25:32.240
and raising questions
perhaps in the conversations

00:25:32.240 --> 00:25:34.270
we have with others.

00:25:34.270 --> 00:25:36.560
And there's also then the
celebratory acceptance

00:25:36.560 --> 00:25:40.940
of welcoming in not defining
others, of welcoming

00:25:40.940 --> 00:25:43.875
in one's own self definition,
whatever that might be,

00:25:43.875 --> 00:25:45.500
and of all of it
being OK because we're

00:25:45.500 --> 00:25:48.730
each masterpieces in the making.

00:25:48.730 --> 00:25:51.650
Drag communicates that to
the audience, that that's

00:25:51.650 --> 00:25:54.680
what we are, whoever we are,
and whatever experiences

00:25:54.680 --> 00:25:56.720
we might be having
in life or have had,

00:25:56.720 --> 00:26:00.110
whatever pain we might
be in, and the joys, too.

00:26:00.110 --> 00:26:01.640
This is an art form
that celebrates

00:26:01.640 --> 00:26:03.980
the beauty of every
person and connects us

00:26:03.980 --> 00:26:08.872
into one fabric of humanity
because this is who we are.

00:26:08.872 --> 00:26:10.628
And here's Anisa Love.

